# Markdown Style Guide

## Overview

This guide defines our markdown style rules for consistent documentation.

## File Structure

### 1. Frontmatter

```yaml
---
description: 'Use single quotes for strings'
globs: '**/*.{md,mdc}'
---
```

### 2. Document Structure

- One H1 (`#`) per document
- Proper heading hierarchy (H1 -> H2 -> H3)
- Sections in logical order
- Clear section transitions
- No duplicate headings

## Formatting Rules

### 1. Headings

- Blank line before headings
- Blank line after headings
- No trailing spaces
- No punctuation at end
- Proper hierarchy levels
- Clear, concise text

### 2. Lists

- Blank line before lists
- Use `-` for unordered lists
- Consistent indentation (2 spaces)
- No trailing spaces
- Proper item alignment
- Clear item text

### 3. Code Blocks

- Specify language
- Proper indentation
- No trailing spaces
- Clear examples
- Meaningful comments
- Consistent style

### 4. Links

- Use reference style for internal links
- MDC format for rule links
- Clear link text
- No trailing spaces
- Proper spacing
- Working references

### 5. Spacing

- Single blank line between sections
- No multiple blank lines
- No trailing spaces
- Use spaces, not tabs
- Consistent indentation
- Clean line endings

## Best Practices

### 1. Content Organization

- Clear hierarchy
- Logical grouping
- Consistent structure
- Progressive disclosure
- Related content links

### 2. Writing Style

- Clear language
- Consistent tone
- Technical accuracy
- Proper terminology
- Concise explanations

### 3. Code Examples

- Clear purpose
- Minimal examples
- Proper context
- Consistent style
- Helpful comments

### 4. Documentation

- Up-to-date content
- Version alignment
- Clear updates
- Proper references
- Maintained links

